                        "co_curator": null,
                        "description": "China’s \"new normal\" growth model has been consumption-led rather than investment-driven - changing the world's second-largest economy from a low-cost manufacturer to a value-added developer of technology and services. Improving its manufacturing prowess and promoting its companies on the international stage are government goals, as are the ambitious “Belt and Road” and “Made in China 2025” initiatives focused on infrastructure and industry. While COVID-19 initially created serious challenges in terms of trade and economic expansion, the country has reported significant GDP growth in 2021.",
