                        "description": "The management of financial and monetary systems is intimately connected to global risk - in the form of potential market meltdowns or pandemics. In the wake of the global financial crisis more than a decade ago, populist movements cast doubt on monetary institutions like the euro, and critics questioned efforts made by central banks to inject liquidity into markets via asset purchasing programs. Now, these institutions and efforts are being relied upon to help keep international financial waters calm despite the devastating impacts of COVID-19.",
